The paper deals with the identification and approximation of fully nonlinear layer neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the structure identification and uniform approximation of two hidden layer neural networks, which is a subfield of deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of neural networks for image classification, which falls under the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with optimization and control problems, which are relevant to the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
